# üåø How to Check Branch Name in Git

This guide explains different ways to check your current branch name in
Git.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ‚úÖ Method 1 --- Show Current Branch (Common Method)

``` bash
git branch
```

Example output:

    * main
      feature-login

The branch with `*` is your current branch.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ‚úÖ Method 2 --- Show Only Current Branch Name (Recommended)

``` bash
git branch --show-current
```

Example output:

    main

This command prints only the branch name.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ‚úÖ Method 3 --- Using Git Status

``` bash
git status
```

Example output:

    On branch main

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## üß† Summary

  Command                     Purpose
  --------------------------- -------------------------------------------
  git branch                  Shows all branches and highlights current
  git branch --show-current   Shows only current branch name
  git status                  Shows branch along with repository status

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ‚≠ê Best Practice

Use:

``` bash
git branch --show-current
```

It is the simplest and cleanest way to check your branch name.
